<div class="context">
<h1 class="title">Pseudo Variables</h1>
<span class="subtitle"></span>
<!-- $$$mkspecs-pseudo-variable-reference.html-description -->
<div class="descr"> <a name="details"></a>
<a name="build-mode"></a>
<h2 id="build-mode">BUILD_MODE</h2>
<p>Contains the mode in which the target is being built. If <code>debug_and_release</code> option is enabled, this variable is empty during meta-target generation pass.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">CONFIG += debug_and_release
DESTDIR = &quot;builds/${BUILD_MODE}&quot;

# in meta-target generation pass: DESTDIR = &quot;builds&quot;
# in debug target build pass: DESTDIR = &quot;builds/debug&quot;
# in release target build pass: DESTDIR = &quot;builds/release&quot;</pre>
<a name="library-mode"></a>
<h2 id="library-mode">LIBRARY_MODE</h2>
<p>Library target only. If <code>static_and_shared</code> option is enabled, contains the type of library taken into account when the target is being built. This variable is empty during meta-target generation pass.</p>
<p>For example:</p>
<pre class="cpp">TEMPLATE = lib
CONFIG += static_and_shared
DESTDIR = &quot;builds/${LIBRARY_MODE}&quot;

# in meta-target generation pass: DESTDIR = &quot;builds&quot;
# in static target build pass: DESTDIR = &quot;builds/static&quot;
# in shared target build pass: DESTDIR = &quot;builds/shared&quot;</pre>
</div>
<!-- @@@mkspecs-pseudo-variable-reference.html -->
